---
const modules = [
  "SwiftUI app shell",
  "PinesCore contracts",
  "GRDB persistence",
  "MLX runtime bridge",
  "Cloud providers",
  "MCP client",
  "Tool policy gate",
  "Watch protocol",
];
---

<section class="section builders" id="builders">
  <div class="builder-copy">
    <span class="section-kicker">Open To Inspect</span>
    <h2>The product story is backed by a source-available Swift codebase.</h2>
    <p>
      Pines is not a black-box landing page. The repository includes the SwiftUI app,
      shared core contracts, persistence, runtime bridges, model lifecycle services,
      policy-gated tools, and Watch support.
    </p>
    <div class="builder-actions">
      <a class="button primary" href="https://github.com/RNT56/pines">View source</a>
      <a class="button secondary" href="https://github.com/RNT56/pines/blob/main/DEV_README.md">Developer README</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="module-board" aria-label="Pines implementation modules">
    {modules.map((module) => <span>{module}</span>)}
  </div>
</section>
